.TH SCROLLLOCK\-LED\-DAEMON 8 "2026-07-03" "1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \- daemon that synchronizes the Scroll Lock key with the keyboard LED
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B scrolllock\-led\-daemon
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scroll Lock LED Daemon monitors the Scroll Lock key for press events
and toggles the corresponding keyboard LED. It runs as a background
service managed by systemd. When the keyboard is disconnected, it waits
and automatically reconnects.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-device \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Keyboard device path (e.g. /dev/input/event4).
Overrides auto\-detection.
.TP
.B \-\-led \fI\,PATH\/\fR
LED brightness file
(e.g. /sys/class/leds/input4::scrolllock/brightness).
Overrides auto\-detection.
.TP
.B \-\-set \fI\,on|off\/\fR
Set the LED state and exit (one\-shot mode).
.TP
.B \-\-toggle
Toggle the LED state and exit (one\-shot mode).
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/scrolllock\-led\-daemon.service
systemd service unit.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Initiate a graceful shutdown.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0
on success, or
.B 1
on failure.
.SH AUTHOR
Alan Santos
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd (1),
.BR evdev (7)
